SCILLY CAY was forwardly placed on the outside, chased four then three wide on the turn, spun four wide into the stretch and capitulated. REED KAN pressed the pace on the outside, turned up the pressure in the three path on the turn, took the lead coming to the quarter-pole, fought outside of a foe under a drive in upper stretch, lost the advantage to the winner approaching the furlong marker, sustained an injury to the right foreleg at the sixteenth-pole and fell then was vanned off.

HOWE STREET was rated just off the pace on the inside, drafted behind foes on the far turn, was given his cue outside the quarter-pole, came out into upper stretch, chased behind the leaders into the final furlong, moved out from behind those foes nearing the sixteenth-pole and also finished with good courage but just missed the trifecta. VERSTAPPEN was reserved under a hold on the inside, came under a drive in upper stretch and lacked the needed kick. VALUE ENGINEERING went three wide on the first turn, was rated outside but with the benefit of cover, went around the far turn in the two path, was roused late on that bend and came up empty.

ATHENRY coaxed from the gate, chased along the inside under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, proved no match for the top one while keeping on to secure the place honors. FEATHERS ROAD chased along the inside down the backstretch and then just off the inside through the turn under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, went eight wide into upper stretch and offered up a mild kick. SANDRONE coaxed from the gate, chased along the inside, got set down angled three to four wide into upper stretch and weakened in the late stages. KING MOONRACER two to three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, bid five wide into upper stretch, flattened out inside the final furlong. STARQUIST chased just off the inside under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled seven wide into upper stretch, offered no response. POWER ATTACK chased along the inside under coaxing from the three-eighths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, came up empty. HEYMACKIT'SJACK cut a swift pace from the three path, went three wide into upper stretch, bowed out near the eighth pole when TWENTY SIX BLACK took over and was not persevered with to the finish backing away spent.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CANDY MAN ROCKET showed speed on the outside then dropped just off the pace, stalked the leading duo in the three path on the turn, was asked late on that bend, gained to make a bid into upper stretch, took a short advantage while remaining on his inside lead at the furlong marker and inched clear under strong urging while continuing on the inside lead to the finish. TWISTED RIDE was hustled from the gate, showed in front early, lost the lead near the nine-sixteenths, vied outside from that point then in the two path on the turn, gained a short lead coming to the quarter-pole, was put to a drive in upper stretch, lost the advantage to the winner at the furlong marker and was outfinished while able to hold the place. STAGE LEFT broke a half-step slow then dropped back, settled off the pace, was roused in the two path on the turn, turned into upper stretch under a drive and finished willingly for the show. DRAFTED bumped with a foe at the start and was off a half-step slow, moved out while settling off the early pace, raced inside early on the turn then shifted three wide later on that bend, came five wide into the stretch and lacked the needed response. BEREN bumped with a rival at the start then was hustled, moved up to get the lead near the nine-sixteenths then vied inside of a foe, raced inside on the turn, lost the lead nearing the quarter-pole, battled under a drive into the final furlong and gave way. MR PHIL settled just off the pace on the outside, was roused four wide on the turn and failed to rally.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPANSIVE established the front shortly after the start and showed the way in hand just off the inside, came under coaxing near the quarter pole and took the inside route into upper stretch, dug in under a drive holding well and safe to the finish kept busy to the end. JUNIPER'S MOON three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled four to five wide into upper stretch, ran on willingly through to the finish to chase the winner home while clear for the place honors. FREE LOOK two to three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled five wide into upper stretch and improved position to secure the show honors. GET YOUR KICKS a bit fractious in the gate prior to the start, chased three wide patiently handled until set down continuing three wide into upper stretch, weakened in the late stages. ALPHA BELLA stumbled at the start recovering outwards and bumping ESSAOUIRA into TRYINMYHEARTOUT, chased along the inside coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch and weakened in the late going. TRYINMYHEARTOUT broke in at the start bumping ESSAOURIA and pinching back STEPHANIE'S CHARM in tandem with that foe, chased just off the inside under a ride from three furlongs out, swung four wide into upper stretch and made no headway. STEPHANIE'S CHARM got bumped between foes and was pinched back at the start, chased three then four wide coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled six wide into upper stretch and offered no rally. BENGALA JOY tracked from just off the inside just off the pace, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, cornered three wide into upper stretch and weakened. ESSAOUIRA got bumped at the start by ALPHA BELLA, then pinched back STEPHANIE'S CHARM before coming together to bump with TRYINMYHEARTOUT, chased three wide under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, angled four to five wide into upper stretch and made no impact. LA VITA SOFIA chased along the inside under coaxing from the three-eighths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch and weakened. BINSKY shied in at the start and was corrected, chased along the inside, tipped out to be four wide midway on the turn, took the inside route into upper stretch and trailed throughout.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOSS OF ALL was hustled from the gate then settled off the pace, saved ground around the turn, swung four wide into the stretch then rallied on the outside, closed strongly into the final furlong, drifted in and bumped the runner-up while taking the lead outside the sixteenth-pole then edged away under good handling. CENTRAL SPEED pressed the pace on the outside then in the two path on the turn, took a short lead near the five-sixteenths, was asked for her best in upper stretch, led under a drive while still on her inside lead into the final furlong, was bumped by the winner while being collared outside the sixteenth-pole then switched to the proper lead and was outfinished while able to get the place. LINARITE settled off the pace, tucked into the two path for the run around the turn, swung six wide into the stretch and improved for the show. FOLLOW THE FED settled towards the rear, saved ground on the turn, came three wide into the stretch and also improved position. GEORGE'S VICE was rated while well placed towards the front, saved ground for most of the turn then shifted to the two path, chased the leader under a drive into the final furlong and weakened. MO DAMORNINGGROUCH was forwardly placed on the outside, dropped back four then five wide on the turn and failed to threaten. MA MI JO DREAMS settled between horses, went three to four wide on the turn and failed to rally. NEVER PERSONAL brushed the outside of the gate at the start, settled just off the pace, went two then three wide on the turn, dropped back five wide into the stretch and capitulated. CAIAROSSA bumped with a rival at the start and was off slow, spotted the front a few lengths, lagged at the rear, went around the turn in the two path, came four wide into the stretch and was no factor. IRISH EMPRESS took a right turn at the start and hit the gate then bumped with a foe while off slow, spotted the front a few lengths, went around the turn in the two path and never reached contention. RENT CONTROL went to the front, set the pace under pressure to her outside, vied along the rail on the turn, lost the lead near the five-sixteenths and faded. SARAH'S DIALED IN was off slow and spotted the front a few lengths, settled well back on the outside, dropped well behind while faltering on the turn, floated well out in the course late on that bend and was eased in the stretch but walked off.
